The paper discusses the adaptation of recurrent neural networks to deal with unevenly sampled system observations, which is a problem commonly encountered in system identification. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SI).
